fields.title: About Me
fields.description_one: I am a dedicated and enthusiastic programmer with a deep passion for the world of coding and software development. From a young age, I have been fascinated by the power of technology and its ability to shape the world we live in. Programming allows me to transform my ideas into tangible solutions, creating innovative and efficient software that solves real-world problems.

fields.service_description: From troubleshooting hardware issues to resolving software conflicts. I am adept at providing comprehensive diagnostics and delivering effective repairs.
Whether you need a simple informational website, an e-commerce platform, or a complex web application, I've got you covered.
With a focus on delivering high-quality, reliable, and secure software applications, I will bring your ideas to life.

fields.Project_info: A tool that allows users to generate strong, random passwords and securely store them along with website credentials. Users can easily generate passwords using a combination of letters, numbers, and symbols. The application provides a convenient way to save website names, email/username, and passwords. Users can also retrieve passwords by searching for the website name. The application ensures that users can efficiently manage their passwords and access them whenever needed.

My first resume website built using Django, HTML5, CSS5 and Bootstrap. Also incorporated OpenAI's GPT-3 Davinci chatbot for users to interact with and ask questions. This website was hosted on Heroku.

A simple form made using Django. This form is used by employees to submit a request for computer repairs. This sends out an automated response via email and sends a copy to a help desk which would be used for further processing of the request.

Travel back in time to a specific year and create a Spotify playlist containing the Billboard Hot 100 songs from that year. It utilizes web scraping with BeautifulSoup to extract the song names from the Billboard website for the specified date. Then, it uses the Spotipy library, which is a lightweight Python library for the Spotify Web API, to search for each song on Spotify and retrieve their unique track URIs. The script authenticates the user with Spotify using the SpotifyOAuth authorization flow, and with the necessary permissions.
Simple province guessing game using the Turtle and Pandas library. Users guesses are logged to a csv file where they can see what provinces they did not get right.

This report use's the Sentinel One REST API as an Azure Function app. It has a timer trigger which looks at a CRON expression. The report creates an xlsx workbook which contains separate worksheets for each branch in the group. The computers have a billing tag and asset tag which makes billing easy and streamlined. The report is sent by SMTP and contains a HTML body which summarizes the data. The API which one can make a get request to provides the asset number and serial number which is used to populate records in SalesForce.
